  <steps>
    <step num="0">Slice chicken breast into cubes. </step>
    <step num="1">In a bowl, combine marinade ingredients. Add chicken and stir to coat. </step>
    <step num="2">Let marinate at least 1 hour. </step>
    <step num="3">In a pan, heat oil on medium-high heat. Remove chicken from marinade with a slotted spoon, and cook all sides until golden brown, about 5 minutes. </step>
    <step num="4">Add sauce ingredients to pan and bring to a boil, mixing continuously, until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes. </step>
    <step num="5">Serve over rice if desired. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
